Students visit different types of educational institutions, reflect on what they have experienced, and articulate their strengths and development areas as learners. Visits to educational institutions also offer the opportunity to get to know potential practice schools.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to enable students to visit different educational institutions, reflect on what they have experienced, and thereby find strengths and areas for development as a learner and, as a result, make more informed choices when studying and when choosing an internship school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student Has visited various types of educational institutions and reflected on what he experienced. Has formulated her/his strengths and areas for development as a learner based on his experience when visiting educational institutions. Makes more informed choices due to visiting educational institutions, including when choosing an practice school.
